            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> in 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[450ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]<strong> </span>boiled water </strong>— this is your <strong>chicken stock</strong></p><p>Once the chicken has browned, add the <strong>chopped ginger</strong>, <strong>chopped chilli</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and your <strong>red Thai curry paste</strong> to the pan and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-1703174647990-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-1703174647990-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-1703174647990-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
